189#define IS_PPC64_TLS_RELOC(R) \
190 (((R) >= R_PPC64_TLS && (R) <= R_PPC64_DTPREL16_HIGHESTA) \
191 || ((R) >= R_PPC64_TPREL16_HIGH && (R) <= R_PPC64_DTPREL16_HIGHA))

194/* e_flags bits specifying ABI.
195 1 for original function descriptor using ABI,
196 2 for revised ABI without function descriptors,
197 0 for unspecified or not using any features affected by the differences. */
198#define EF_PPC64_ABI 3
199
200/* The ELFv2 ABI uses three bits in the symbol st_other field of a
201 function definition to specify the number of instructions between a
202 function's global entry point and local entry point.
203 The global entry point is used when it is necessary to set up the
204 toc pointer (r2) for the function. Callers must enter the global
205 entry point with r12 set to the global entry point address. On
206 return from the function, r2 may have a different value to that
207 which it had on entry.
208 The local entry point is used when r2 is known to already be valid
209 for the function. There is no requirement on r12 when using the
210 local entry point, and on return r2 will contain the same value as
211 at entry.
212 A value of zero in these bits means that the function has a single
213 entry point with no requirement on r12 or r2, and that on return r2
214 will contain the same value as at entry.
215 Values of one and seven are reserved. */
216#define STO_PPC64_LOCAL_BIT 5
217#define STO_PPC64_LOCAL_MASK (7 << STO_PPC64_LOCAL_BIT)
218
219// 3 bit other field to bytes.
220static inline unsigned int
221ppc64_decode_local_entry(unsigned int other)
222{
223 return ((1 << other) >> 2) << 2;
224}
225
226// bytes to field value.
227static inline unsigned int
228ppc64_encode_local_entry(unsigned int val)
229{
230 return (val >= 4 * 4
231 ? (val >= 8 * 4
232 ? (val >= 16 * 4 ? 6 : 5)
233 : 4)
234 : (val >= 2 * 4
235 ? 3
236 : (val >= 1 * 4 ? 2 : 0)));
237}
238
239/* st_other to number of bytes. */
240#define PPC64_LOCAL_ENTRY_OFFSET(other) \
241 ppc64_decode_local_entry (((other) & STO_PPC64_LOCAL_MASK) \
242 >> STO_PPC64_LOCAL_BIT)
243/* number of bytes to st_other. */
244#define PPC64_SET_LOCAL_ENTRY_OFFSET(val) \
245 ppc64_encode_local_entry (val) << STO_PPC64_LOCAL_BIT
246
247/* Specify the start of the .glink section. */
248#define DT_PPC64_GLINK DT_LOPROC
249
250/* Specify the start and size of the .opd section. */
251#define DT_PPC64_OPD (DT_LOPROC + 1)
252#define DT_PPC64_OPDSZ (DT_LOPROC + 2)
253
254/* Specify whether various optimisations are possible. */
255#define DT_PPC64_OPT (DT_LOPROC + 3)
256#define PPC64_OPT_TLS 1
257#define PPC64_OPT_MULTI_TOC 2
258#define PPC64_OPT_LOCALENTRY 4
